      "id": "2e0a2d27cea61a4b",
      "text": "    and finally: I'd say what we need to put forward in a context of a commons-oikonomy (or you name it) is a combination of the latter connected to the idea of a human being as a nested-I; so an communicative, contingent and emotional rationality aware if it's context and interdependency of others and of the ecosystem: one could call it an ubuntu-rationality concepts I've dealt  with in an academic work I've done, so - I translate tech terms and then we can try to find a more accessible language for the idea: please edit this as you see fit and then I integrate it into the wiki\n\n"
