    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "526f65c52e936d7a",
      "text": "    typical for critical institutionalism is a processual rationality ⇒ where reflexion is key, context and process are taken into account and the human being is dowed with the capacity to put its reasoning beyond the calculative rationality in a given/practical/institutional context; sometimes it's called \"practical reasonableness\"\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
