      "text": "    typical for ecological economics (homo oecologicus) is a processual, co-evolutionary and contingent (? ergebnisoffen) rationality, where the embededness, our being part of socio-ecological systems that are \"beyond and above us\" is taken into account\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b456732f99376218",
      "text": "    typical for feminist approaches to economy is a combination of practical, communicative and emotional rationality; so that sensing/ feeling nurtures our reasons for acting\n"
    },
