        "text": "The question which logic and mindset is at work when we act, has been central to Western intellectual culture. We strangly defer to this as \"rationality\". And we live in a world where the dominant idea of mainstream economists is, that our actions (on the market) are usually \"rational\" according to a calculation of costs and benefits. But \"rational\" and \"irrational\" are  meaningless with respect to out subjective goals, and more meaningless with respect to human interaction in complex and adaptive socio-ecological systems. \n"
